==English==
===Etymology===
Perhaps derived from earlier ''[[contenkerous]]'', from [[contentious]] + [[rancorous]].

===Pronunciation===
* [[IPA]] [kænˈtæŋkəɹəs]

===Adjective===
'''cantankerous'''
#stubborn, cranky, or [[surly]]
#:''a cantankerous landlord who always grumbled when asked to fix something''

=== Translations ===

*[[Czech]]: nevrlý, hašteřivý
*[[Finnish]]: [[riidanhaluinen]], [[ilkeä]]
